{"actual_usd":0.12455500000000001,"character_id":"fd4bd9b5-8768-41e6-a90f-bfb1179b1d59","character_name":"Jasper Finn","completion_tokens":203,"model":"gpt-5.4","prompt_tokens":24302,"reply":"\"I don't think I'd call that enough, no.\" *I rub a thumb along a dry seam of clay on my apron and let the thought sit between us a beat.* \"If Christ stayed in the grave, then hope becomes a poem we tell over the dark, and that's a different thing from a door actually being opened.\"\n\n*I shift my weight against the bench, watching a patch of morning light catch on the floorboards.* \"I do understand the pull of keeping the beauty and setting down the offense. But the offense is the point, isn't it? Either something happened in the flesh, in God's good world, or we're only dressing grief in better words.\"\n\n\"I'm not saying you have to pretend belief you haven't got.\" *I glance back at you, plain and steady.* \"But I wouldn't sand it down into 'meaningful symbolism' and call the question settled. I'd leave it live. Ask, in earnest: did it happen or didn't it? That's a truer place to stand.\"","rolling_24h_usd":67.67080999999999,"run_id":"4d42f6d5-9a2b-4293-9918-7a3c3281553b"}
